Class InsertionMapper<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • piiksuma.database.Mapper<E>
      • piiksuma.database.InsertionMapper<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - Mapped class type. Used to check asigments when returning query results. 

    public class InsertionMapper<E>
extends Mapper<E>
    Database conection and data insertion wrapper. Performs insertions from given objects without actually specifying SQL sentences.
    Author:
    luastan, CardamaS99, danimf99, alvrogd, OswaldOswin1, Marcos-marpin

      • insert

        public void insert()
            throws PiikDatabaseException
        Inserts all the given elements into the database. When following foreign keys while inserting; It won't go into infinite recursion. At most It will propperly insert a foreign key from a foreign key. For example: A post wich has a parent wich is partially identified by its user which is actually a custom declared Class, not a String or an integer.
        Throws:
        PiikDatabaseException
